{"questionId":"9074776","questionHtml":"<p>Two copper wires of equal lengths but different diameters are used to connect a cell to a load.&nbsp;Wire 1 has a diameter <em>M</em>, wire 2 has a diameter 2<em>M</em>. The electron drift velocities in wires 1 and 2 are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>What is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p><br>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9074776","referenceCode":"22N.1.HL.TZ0.16","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two copper wires of equal lengths but different diameters are used to connect a cell to a load. Wire 1 has a diameter M, wire 2 has a diameter 2M. The electron drift velocities in ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"16","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.1 – Electric fields","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}